==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Farandole
<hw>Fa`ran`dole"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>farandole</ets>, Pr. <ets>farandoulo</ets>.]</ety> <def>A rapid
dance in six-eight time in which a large number join hands and dance in
various figures, sometimes moving from room to room. It originated in
Provence.</def></p>

<p><q>I have pictured them dancing a sort of <qex>farandole</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>W. D. Howells.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Farantly</ent>⟦br⟧
